ABAKALIKI – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) presidential screening Committee has satisfied former Secretary to government of the Federation, Senator Anyim Pius Anyim, qualified to stand for the Party’s President Primary election. Anyim, and other PDP presidential Aspirants were screened by the committee on Friday in Abuja. In his official Facebook wall, Anyim on Saturday, announced that he was cleared by the Committee. The Presidential hopeful also displayed the certificate of clearance issue to him by the Committee on Facebook wall. Anyim said: “The PDP Presidential Screening Committee has certified me qualified to stand for the Presidential Primary Election at the 2022 Special National Convention. “My special appreciation goes out to the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP National Working Committee, Board of Trustees and all other organs of our great party for their massive support and kind disposition towards myself and my fellow candidates throughout the pre- primaries stage.” The PDP Presidential screening committee had on Friday while speaking with Journalists announced that it disqualified two Presidential Aspirants; a development that sent jitters in the spines of the Aspirants and their supporters.